<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="491" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,150,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[523,650,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Figs. 4c–d</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[709,779,151,177]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">China</collectingCountry>
, the species is known from 
<collectingRegion box="[1118,1194,151,177]" country="China" name="Henan" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Henan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1210,1282,151,177]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Gansu</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1346,1436,151,177]" country="China" name="Qinghai" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Qinghai</collectingRegion>
provinces, and 
<collectingRegion box="[325,466,187,213]" country="China" name="Ningxia" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Ningxia Hui</collectingRegion>
Autonomous Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Li, W. H." box="[723,917,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" refId="ref4770" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Li, W. H. (2018) Species Catalogue of China. Volume 2 Animals, Insecta (III), Plecoptera. Science Press, Beijing, 71 pp." type="book" year="2018">Yang &amp; Li 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Originally it was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1316,1383,187,213]" name="Japan" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Japan</collectingCountry>
, and known also from 
<collectingCountry box="[349,417,223,249]" name="South Korea" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Korea</collectingCountry>
and the Russian Far East (
<bibRefCitation author="Shimizu, T." box="[717,878,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" pagination="213 - 225" refId="ref4052" refString="Shimizu, T. (1994) Taxonomic changes and synonyms for the East Asian species of the genus Nemoura (Plecoptera: Nemouridae). Aquatic Insects, 16 (4), 213 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 01650429409361558" type="journal article" year="1994">Shimizu 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hwang, J. M. &amp; Muranyi, D. &amp; Bae, Y. J." box="[889,1100,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" pagination="176 - 178" refId="ref3232" refString="Hwang, J. M., Muranyi, D. &amp; Bae, Y. J. (2016) New records of Plecoptera from Korea. Entomological Research Bulletin, 32 (2), 176 - 178." type="journal article" year="2016">
Hwang 
<emphasis box="[977,1034,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhiltzova, L. A." box="[1111,1287,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" refId="ref4982" refString="Zhiltzova, L. A. (2003) Vesnyanki (Plecoptera) gruppa Euholognatha. Nauka, St. Petersburg, 538 pp." type="book" year="2003">Zhiltzova 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The present specimens are the first records for Qinghai Province. Usually it occupies upper rhitral habitat similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wu" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Nemouridae" genus="Nemoura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Nemoura geei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the collecting site in Huzhu County is the larger headwater of Baimuxia River (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1228,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[307,1281,181,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[307,1281,181,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Nemoura habitats in Qinghai, China. A. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov. and Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Deqian Village. B. Habitat of Nemoura jixiangwangi sp. nov.: Dayu Village. C. Habitat of Nemoura geei Wu, 1929 and Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Sigou. D. Habitat of Nemoura papilla Okamoto, 1922: Huzhu County, Weibei Highway. E–F. Habitat of Nemoura securigera Klapálek, 1907: Qihankaigou (Qihankai valley), main river and sidestream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6899855" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6899855/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="491">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
